name: StandardSetController
description: StandardSetController objects allow you to create list controllers similar to, or as extensions of, the pre-built Visualforce list controllers provided by Salesforce.

cancel().name: cancel
cancel().description: Returns the PageReference of the original page, if known, or the home page.

first().name: first
first().description: Returns the first page of records.

getcompleteresult().name: getCompleteResult
getcompleteresult().description: Indicates whether there are more records in the set than the maximum record limit. If this is false, there are more records than you can process using the list controller. The maximum record limit is 10,000 records.

getfilterid().name: getFilterId
getfilterid().description: Returns the ID of the filter that is currently in context.

gethasnext().name: getHasNext
gethasnext().description: Indicates whether there are more records after the current page set.

gethasprevious().name: getHasPrevious
gethasprevious().description: Indicates whether there are more records before the current page set.

getlistviewoptions().name: getListViewOptions
getlistviewoptions().description: Returns a list of the listviews available to the current user.

getpagenumber().name: getPageNumber
getpagenumber().description: Returns the page number of the current page set. Note that the first page returns 1.

getpagesize().name: getPageSize
getpagesize().description: Returns the number of records included in each page set.

getrecord().name: getRecord
getrecord().description: Returns the sObject that represents the changes to the selected records. This retrieves the prototype object contained within the class, and is used for performing mass updates.

getrecords().name: getRecords
getrecords().description: Returns the list of sObjects in the current page set. This list is immutable, i.e. you can't call clear() on it.

getresultsize().name: getResultSize
getresultsize().description: Returns the number of records in the set.

getselected().name: getSelected
getselected().description: Returns the list of sObjects that have been selected.

last().name: last
last().description: Returns the last page of records.

next().name: next
next().description: Returns the next page of records.

previous().name: previous
previous().description: Returns the previous page of records.

save().name: save
save().description: Inserts new records or updates existing records that have been changed. After this operation is finished, it returns a PageReference to the original page, if known, or the home page.

setfilterid(string).name: setFilterID
setfilterid(string).description: Sets the filter ID of the controller.

setpagesize(integer).name: setPageSize
setpagesize(integer).description: Sets the number of records in each page set.

standardsetcontroller(database.queryloca.name: StandardSetController
standardsetcontroller(database.queryloca.description: Creates an instance of the ApexPages.StandardSetController class for the list of objects returned by the query locator.

querylocator.name: queryLocator
querylocator.description: A query locator representing a list of sObjects.

standardsetcontroller(list<sobject>).name: StandardSetController
standardsetcontroller(list<sobject>).description: Creates an instance of the ApexPages.StandardSetController class for the specified list of standard or custom objects.

controllersobjects.name: controllerSObjects
controllersobjects.description: A List of standard or custom objects.
